  "text": "In the largest analysis of transcriptomic data pertaining to transplant tolerance, Li and colleagues extended previous work by developing a tolerance signature independent of recipient age and donor source, cause of end-stage liver disease, or concomitant viral infection [CITATION_1] . This was achieved through the amalgamation of living and deceased donor and pediatric, as well as adult data from across different clinical centers. The 13-gene tolerance signature identified (Table 1 ) was highly associated with NK cells, corroborating earlier work, and proved to have striking predictive accuracy, exhibiting 100% sensitivity and 83% specificity. This degree of predictive capacity would appear to obviate the need for the biopsy derived gene signatures, thought to be of superior utility as biomarkers of tolerance in earlier studies [CITATION_2] .",
